prop.name: dataFeedElement
prop.desc: An item within in a data feed. Data feeds may have many elements.

Dataset.name: includedInDataCatalog
Dataset.desc: A data catalog which contains this dataset.

Dataset.name: datasetTimeInterval
Dataset.desc: The range of temporal applicability of a dataset, e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 (in ISO 8601 time interval format).

Dataset.name: catalog
Dataset.desc: A data catalog which contains this dataset.

Dataset.name: issn
Dataset.desc: The International Standard Serial Number (ISSN) that identifies this serial publication. You can repeat this property to identify different formats of, or the linking ISSN (ISSN-L) for, this serial publication.

Dataset.name: spatial
Dataset.desc: The range of spatial applicability of a dataset, e.g. for a dataset of New York weather, the state of New York.

Dataset.name: temporal
Dataset.desc: The range of temporal applicability of a dataset, e.g. for a 2011 census dataset, the year 2011 (in ISO 8601 time interval format).

Dataset.name: includedDataCatalog
Dataset.desc: A data catalog which contains this dataset (this property was previously 'catalog', preferred name is now 'includedInDataCatalog').

Dataset.name: distribution
Dataset.desc: A downloadable form of this dataset, at a specific location, in a specific format.
